Create a Simple Web Page

Objective:
--Build a basic personal info webpage that includes:
1.A heading and paragraph
2.An image
3.Some links
4.A structured layout using <div>

Example Code – My Simple Web Page

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>My Simple Web Page</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }
      .header {
        background-color: #333;
        color: white;
        padding: 20px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .main {
        padding: 20px;
      }
      .profile-img {
        width: 150px;
        border-radius: 50%;
      }
      .footer {
        background-color: #f2f2f2;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 10px;
        margin-top: 20px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>

    <div class="header">
      <h1>Hello! I'm [Your Name]</h1>
      <p>Welcome to my first HTML web page</p>
    </div>

    <div class="main">
      <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/150" alt="My Photo" class="profile-img">
      <p>I am currently learning <strong>HTML</strong> as part of a 30-day challenge.</p>
      <p>Here are some of my favorite websites:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.google.com" target="_blank">Google</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.w3schools.com" target="_blank">W3Schools</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
      <p>© 2025 [Your Name]</p>
    </div>

  </body>
</html>

Notes:
--Replace [Your Name] with your real name.
--You can use a real image or keep the placeholder.
--This combines everything you've learned up to Day 12!
